name: float_f64_negative_zero
description: |
  IEEE 754 binary64 negative zero has only the sign bit set. Numeric equality
  normally treats it as equal to positive zero, while 1 / -0 produces negative
  infinity under the default IEEE rules. Serialization, hashing, formatting,
  and sign-sensitive algorithms may therefore expose its distinct bit pattern.
format: hex
decode-as: f64-le
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f64"
  - "signed-zero"
---
00 00 00 00 00 00 00 80   # 0x8000000000000000: -0
